    <milestone unit="tei:head" spanTo="#loan_ms_70_08-0004.02"/>
    <line rend="indent2">To Laughter—</line>
    <anchor xml:id="loan_ms_70_08-0004.02"/>
    <line>Thy friends were never mine thou heartless</line>
    <line rend="indent4">fiend:</line>
    <line>Silence and solitude &#x26; calm &#x26; storm,</line>
    <line>Hope, before whose veiled shrine all</line>
    <line rend="indent3">spirits bend</line>
    <line>In worship, &#x26; the rainbow vested form</line>
    <line>Of concience, that within thy hollow heart </line>
    <line>Can find no throne—the love of such great </line>
    <line rend="indent4">powers</line>
    <line>Which ha<mod><del rend="overwritten">ve</del><add place="intralinear">s</add></mod> requited mine in many hours</line>
    <line>Of loneliness, thou ne’er hast felt; depart!</line>
    <line>Thou canst not bear the moons great eye, thou</line>
    <line rend="indent4">fearest</line>
    <line>A fair child clothed in smiles—aught that is high </line>
    <line>Or good or beautiful.—Thy voice is dearest</line>
    <line>To those who mock at truth &#x26; Innocency</line>
    <line>I, now alone, weep without shame to see</line>
    <line>How many broken hearts lie bare to thee.</line>
  </zone>
